HEADWORD: Corporality
<hw>Cor`po*ral"i*ty</hw> <pr>(k?r`p?-r?l"l?-t?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>:
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Corporalities</plw> <pr>(-t<?/z)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[L. <ets>corporalitas</ets>: cf. F.<ets>corporalit<?/</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being or having a body; bodily existence;
corporeality; -- opposed to <xex>spirituality</xex>.</def> <rj><au>Dr.
H. More.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A confraternity; a guild.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corporally</ent>⟦br⟧
